            onto its thick<br> atmosphere—a necessary component in preventing any prospective oceans from vanishing into
            space.</li>

        <li><strong>Astronomical Location</strong>: TAt roughly 100 light-years from Earth, this planet is
            well-positioned for follow-up <br> studies with contemporary space telescopes like the James Webb Space
            Telescope, which might study its <br> atmosphere. It is part of the Draco constellation.​ </li>

        <li><strong>Twin Start System</strong>: TOI 1452 b is a member of a binary system of stars. Long-period orbits
            of the companion <br> star of its host star may have long-term effects on the planet's temperature and orbital
            dynamics.
        </li>
